> We've sent you two kinds of flaky, savory empanadas! Half are filled with seasoned ground beef and veggies, and the rest are filled with margherita pizza flavors (like tomato sauce, basil, and mozzarella). These Latin American pastries are the perfect appetizer or snack for any mealtime or gathering. All you have to do is bake or air fry them to golden perfection and share! We like to dip them in sour cream and salsa, but feel free to serve them with your favorite dips and toppings.

> Keep refrigerated until ready to eat; best if used within 7 days.

== Oven Method ==

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 375 degrees. Place the
@Maspandas Pizza Empanadas{7.5%ounce} and @Maspandas Beef Empanadas{7.5%ounce}
on a lightly greased #baking sheet{}. Bake on middle rack, flipping
halfway through, until golden brown, ~{15-18%minutes}.

> Oven times may vary.

== Air Fryer Method ==

Coat an #air fryer basket{} with nonstick cooking spray. Arrange
empanadas side by side in basket (you may have to work in batches). Air fry
at 375 degrees until golden brown, ~{8-10%minutes}.